---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy | Psychopedagogical Society";
const description =
    "Privacy Policy of the Psychopedagogical Society. Data processing rules, GDPR, user rights.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} lang="en">
    <Header lang="en" />

    <main class="page-container">
        <div class="container animate-fade-in">
            <header class="page-header">
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="subtitle">Psychopedagogical Society (TPP)</p>
                <p class="meta">Effective from: 01.01.2026</p>
            </header>

            <div class="content">
                <section>
                    <h2>I. General Provisions</h2>
                    <p>
                        This Privacy Policy explains the rules for collecting
                        and processing personal data of Users and Clients of the
                        Psychopedagogical Society (TPP). The document is based
                        on the GDPR and Polish law.
                    </p>
                    <div class="alert-box">
                        <p>
                            <strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Services provided by TPP
                            are of psychosocial counselling, education, and support
                            nature. They do not constitute health services within
                            the meaning of the Act on Medical Activity; therefore,
                            collected data is not "medical records" but client support
                            documentation.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>II. Data Controller</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Data Controller is <strong
                            >Towarzystwo Psychopedagogiczne</strong
                        > based in Bolesławiec (59‑700), ul. Warszawska 1/3, Poland.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Contact: <a href="mailto:rodo@psychopedagog.org"
                            >rodo@psychopedagog.org</a
                        >.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>III. Scope and Purpose</h2>
                    <p>
                        We process data necessary to provide counselling and
                        training services:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>ID Data:</strong> Name, surname, tax ID (for invoices),
                            contact details.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Sensitive Data (Art. 9 GDPR):</strong> Information
                            about life situation, family, mood, and support needs
                            – processed solely based on your explicit consent (service
                            contract) to fulfill the service.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Service execution (support, opinions,
                        training), accounting, and defense against claims.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>IV. Retention Period</h2>
                    <p>
                        We do not apply medical record retention periods (20
                        years) as we are not a medical entity.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Session Notes / Opinions:</strong> Stored for
                            2 years after the end of cooperation (limitation period
                            for civil claims).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Financial Documents:</strong> 5 years from the
                            end of the tax year.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        After this time, data is permanently deleted or
                        anonymized.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>V. Recipients and Transfer</h2>
                    <p>
                        Access to data is granted to authorized associates
                        (Counsellors), accountants, and IT providers.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Transfer outside EEA:</strong> Due to training and
                        certification cooperation, your data (name, course completion
                        status) may be transferred to a partner entity in Australia.
                        This transfer is necessary for the performance of the contract
                        (certification) or based on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC).
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>VI. User Rights</h2>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to: access, rectify, delete ("right
                        to be forgotten" – unless it conflicts with tax duties
                        or defense of claims), and restrict processing.
                        Complaints can be lodged with the President of UODO
                        (Poland).
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>VII. Cookies and Security</h2>
                    <p>
                        The website uses cookies for statistical and functional
                        purposes. We use SSL encryption and GDPR-compliant data
                        protection procedures.
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>

<style>
    .page-container {
        padding: 8rem 0 4rem;
        min-height: 80vh;
    }

    .page-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 4rem;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        color: var(--color-primary);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .subtitle {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--color-text-light);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .meta {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--color-text-light);
        opacity: 0.8;
    }

    .content {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        background: var(--color-bg-card);
        padding: 3rem;
        border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    }

    section {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    section:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    h2 {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-bg-alt);
    }

    p,
    li {
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }

    ul {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .alert-box {
        background: var(--color-bg-alt);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: var(--radius-md);
        border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
        margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }

    .alert-box p {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    a {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }

    a:hover {
        color: var(--color-accent);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .content {
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }
    }
</style>
